17 and which shall be paid by local units of administration to the various classifications of
18 professional personnel required to be certificated by the Professional Standards
19 Commission. The minimum salary schedule shall provide a minimum salary base for
20 each classification of professional personnel required to be certificated,; shall provide for
21 increment increases above the minimum salary base of each classification based upon
22 individual experience and length of satisfactory service,; and shall include such other
23 uniformly applicable factors as the state board may find relevant to the establishment of
24 such a schedule.
25 (2)(A) Effective July 1, 2026, the The minimum salary base for certificated
26 professional personnel with a bachelor's degrees degree and no experience, when
27 annualized from a ten-month basis to a 12 month basis, shall be comparable to the
28 national average living wage as determined by the State Board of Education of the
29 recent graduates of the University System of Georgia holding bachelor's degrees and
30 entering positions, excluding professional educator teaching positions, in Georgia
31 having educational entry requirements comparable to the requirements for entry into
32 Georgia public school teaching.
33 (B) No less than every three years by December 1, beginning in 2026, the State Board
34 of Education shall:
35 (i) Calculate the national average living wage required under subparagraph (A) of
36 this paragraph utilizing research based data compiled from no less than three
37 nationally recognized authorities; and
38 (ii) Publish on the Department of Education's public website such national average
39 living wage along with an explanation of how such average was calculated including
40 all of the authorities upon which such calculation was based.
41 (3) The placement of teachers on the salary schedule of minimum salaries provided for
42 in this subsection shall be based on certificate level and years of creditable experience,
43 except service; provided, however, that a teacher shall not receive credit for any year of
