48 (4) The General Assembly shall annually appropriate funds to implement a salary
49 schedule for certificated professional personnel. For each state fiscal year, the state board
50 shall adopt the salary schedule for which funding has been appropriated by the General
51 Assembly. A local unit of administration shall not pay to any full-time certificated
52 professional employee a salary less than that prescribed by the schedule of minimum
53 salaries, except as required by this Code section; nor shall a local unit of administration
54 pay to any part-time certificated professional employee less than a pro rata portion of the
55 respective salary prescribed by the schedule of minimum salaries, except as required by
56 this Code section.
57 (5) For purposes of this subsection, an educator's placement on the salary schedule shall
58 not be based on a leadership degree, which shall mean a degree earned in conjunction
59 with completion of an educator leadership preparation program approved by the
60 Professional Standards Commission, unless the educator is employed in a leadership
61 position as defined by the State Board of Education, but shall be placed on the salary
62 schedule position attributable to the educator but for the leadership degree; provided,
63 however, that this shall not apply, regardless of whether or not he or she is in a leadership
64 position, to:
65 (1)(A) An educator who possessed a leadership degree prior to July 1, 2010; or
66 (2)(B) An educator who possessed:
67 (A)(i) A master's level leadership degree prior to July 1, 2012;
68 (B)(ii) An education specialist level leadership degree prior to July 1, 2013; or
69 (C)(iii) A doctoral level leadership degree prior to July 1, 2014, so long as he or she
70 was enrolled in such leadership preparation program on or before April 1, 2009."
